<h2 id='file-paths'>File Paths</h2><h3 id='_modpath'>_modpath</h3><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight lua tab-lua"><code><span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">OpenNetBattle</span>
<span class="err">├─</span> <span class="o">...</span>
<span class="err">└─</span> <span class="n">resources</span>
   <span class="err">└─</span> <span class="n">cards</span>
      <span class="err">└─</span> <span class="n">example_card</span>
         <span class="err">├─</span> <span class="n">entry</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">lua</span>
         <span class="err">└─</span> <span class="n">sub_folder</span>
            <span class="err">└─</span> <span class="n">script</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">lua</span>
</code></pre></div>
<p>This is a <strong><code>string</code></strong> containing the path to <em>the</em> <code>entry.lua</code> <em>file for this package</em>.<br>
&emsp;i.e. For <em>all</em> scripts in a mod, using <code>_modpath</code> <em>will</em> give the same value.</p>

<p><em>In the example on the right,</em> <code>_modpath</code> _will always return <code>resources/cards/example_card/</code>.</p>
<h3 id='_folderpath'>_folderpath</h3><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight lua tab-lua"><code><span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">OpenNetBattle</span>
<span class="err">├─</span> <span class="o">...</span>
<span class="err">└─</span> <span class="n">resources</span>
   <span class="err">└─</span> <span class="n">cards</span>
      <span class="err">└─</span> <span class="n">example_card</span>
         <span class="err">├─</span> <span class="n">entry</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">lua</span>
         <span class="err">└─</span> <span class="n">sub_folder</span>
            <span class="err">└─</span> <span class="n">script</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">lua</span>
</code></pre></div>
<p>This is a <strong><code>string</code></strong> containing the path to <em>the current script file</em>.<br>
&emsp;i.e. For <em>all</em> scripts in a mod, using <code>_modpath</code> <em>might not</em> give the same value.</p>

<p><em>In the example on the right,</em> <code>_folderpath</code> <em>will return:</em><br>
&emsp;In <strong><code>entry.lua</code></strong>: <code>resources/cards/example_card/</code><br>
&emsp;In <strong><code>script.lua</code></strong>: <code>resources/cards/example_card/sub_folder/</code>.</p>
